latestIgtvVideos.caption:
…..and she loved a little boy very very much, even more than she loved herself❤️❤️❤️
…..and just like that he turns 3🥹🥹🥹
Pattu, I love you more than words can describe & heart can fully show✨
I wish you good health, joy, happiness & peace of mind always😘 Happy Birthday AARYAN🫅🏻😍

A few years back, when I was down with some thoughts, my dad came up with a script… He told me to act as an owner of the land & he be the labor. I was not very in the mood to act or have fun whatsoever & he pulled my cousin sisters into the act… I said I can’t say NE, VA, PO,.. he insisted I stick to the script, I took some 8 re-takes & this was going on for 2 hours…
All these are planned just to make me laugh my heart out & that’s my Appa… NO ONE LIKE YOU APPA…  you’ve taught me so many things, you’ve taught me to be independent, intelligent, fun, kind, to treat everyone equally… be it the god or the layman, I should speak to everyone with the same tone with love & respect…  you may be the strict police outside… Still, to me, you’re the most kind, thoughtful soul… 
Thank you for being the best dad & now for being the best grandpa in the whole wide world❤️
I love you to the moon & back🤗😘
Happy Father’s Day to MY HERO🥰
#happyfathersday

latestPosts.caption:
Happy Father’s Day to my Appa… I’ve said it a hundred times, but you truly are the best. And now, you’ve graduated to being the bestest Thatha in the world 💙 I still remember your words:
“Don’t ever let people respect you just for your surname — whether it’s your father’s or your husband’s. Create value for your first name, and let them know you for you.” 🙏🙏
You planted that thought in me so young and it’s shaped the woman I am today. You gave me courage, independence, and belief in myself. And now, watching Aaryan say he wants to become a police officer just like you… it feels like life has come full circle. Love you to infinity, Appa 🫂❤️✨

And Happy Father’s Day to Aaryan’s Appa & Best-friend… Ram, Thank you for being my calm when I can’t be, and for giving Aaryan everything I sometimes fall short of. Everyone says he’s an extrovert like me… but as his Amma, I see the way he mirrors you too — in his quiet strength, his patience, his kind heart 🥹✨ I always joke that he might look like you, but his soul is mine. But today, I’ll admit… he’s the perfect blend of both of us. So yes, it’s your win today ☺️😘✨

I’m just so incredibly lucky to be surrounded by these amazing men - Aaryan, Appa & Ram - My Main Men, forever 🖤❤️🤍👨‍👧‍👦🧿🪬🧿✨

#Happyfathersday #Gratefulforthemeninmylife
